<div class="smd-page">

  <header class="smd-page__header">
    <h1 class="smd-page__title">Dialogs</h1>
  </header>

  <section class="smd-page__body">

    <p>Here is an example of a alert with dismiss and action buttons in the header.</p>

    <p>{{smd-button text='Open default alert' action="showDefaultAlert"}}</p>

    {{code-snippet name="smd-alert.hbs"}}

    <p>Here is an example of a alert with dismiss and action buttons in the header.</p>

    <p>{{smd-button text='Open alert with title' action="showTitleAlert"}}</p>

    {{code-snippet name="smd-alert-title.hbs"}}

    <p>Here is an example of a alert with dismiss and action buttons in the header.</p>

    <p>{{smd-button text='Open naked alert' action="showNakedAlert"}}</p>

    {{code-snippet name="smd-alert-naked.hbs"}}

  </section>

  <header class="smd-page__header">
    <h1 class="smd-page__title">Dialog Service</h1>
  </header>

  <section class="smd-page__body">
    <p>The dialog service can be injected into your components and routes to control them. Typically this means you will use the service to open and close your alert dialogs.</p>

    <p>Each instance should be given an id (string) in your template to use as a unique reference from your routes & components.</p>

    {{code-snippet name="smd-alert.js"}}

    <h2 class="smd-page__subtitle">Open alert</h2>

    <p>Call <em>showAlert(id)</em> to display an alert dialog on screen.</p>

    {{code-snippet name="smd-alert-show.js"}}

    <h2 class="smd-page__subtitle">Hide alert</h2>

    <p>Call <em>hideAlert(id)</em> to hide an alert dialog on screen.</p>

    {{code-snippet name="smd-alert-hide.js"}}

  </section>

  <header class="smd-page__header" id="attributes">
    <h1 class="smd-page__title">Attributes</h1>
  </header>

  <section class="smd-page__body">
    <table class="sg-table sg-table--attributes">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Description</th>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>Default</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>title</td>
          <td>The title text for the alert box</td>
          <td><em>string</em></td>
          <td>null</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>affirmativeText</td>
          <td>Text for the confirm button</td>
          <td><em>string</em></td>
          <td>null</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>dismissiveText</td>
          <td>Text for the dismiss button</td>
          <td><em>string</em></td>
          <td>null</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>


  <header class="smd-page__header" id="actions">
    <h1 class="smd-page__title">Actions</h1>
  </header>

  <section class="smd-page__body">
    <table class="sg-table sg-table--actions">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Action</th>
          <th>Description</th>
          <th>Params</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>action</td>
          <td>Default action called when an event is fired and a event specific action has not been defined. Possible types are: confirm & dismiss.</td>
          <td><em>type</em> (string), <em>alert</em> (object)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>affirmativeAction</td>
          <td>If specified this will be called on affimative action.</td>
          <td><em>alert</em> (object)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>dismissiveAction</td>
          <td>If specified this will be called on the dismissive action. By default this is set to false which will just hide the alert on click.</td>
          <td><em>alert</em> (object)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

</div>

{{#smd-alert id="alert" affirmativeText="Delete" dismissiveText="Cancel" affirmativeAction="confirm"}}
  <p>Delete thing?</p>
{{/smd-alert}}

{{#smd-alert id="titleAlert" title="Use Googles location service?" affirmativeText="Agree" dismissiveText="Disagree" affirmativeAction="confirm"}}
<p>Let Google help apps determin location. This means sending anonomus location data to Google, even when no apps are running.</p>
{{/smd-alert}}

{{#smd-alert id="nakedAlert" affirmativeAction="confirm"}}
<p>I am here to alert you.</p>
<p>Are you alerted?</p>
{{/smd-alert}}
